### Footnotes

<span id="fn_618"></span>[103:4](mhm33.htm#fr_618.md) *A famine year:*
Probably A.H. 382 when famine prices prevailed in Baghdad and bread was
40 dirhems a pound (Ibn Al-Athír, ix, 66). A.H. 373, 376 and 377 were
also years of severe drought in ‘Iráq, Ibn Al-Athír, ix.

<span id="fn_619"></span>[103:5](mhm33.htm#fr_619.md) *United:* Literally,
bound together with the string of the Pleiades.

<span id="fn_620"></span>[103:6](mhm33.htm#fr_620.md) *What is thy affair?*
Cf. Qur’án, xx, 96.

<span id="fn_621"></span>[103:7](mhm33.htm#fr_621.md) … *Follow up with:*
Literally, give thee to drink a second time,

<span id="fn_622"></span>[104:1](mhm33.htm#fr_622.md) … *Brinjal:*
Arabicized from the Persian Sanskrit *Banganah*, English Brinjal; the
*Solanum melongena*, mad-apple; or egg-plant.

<span id="fn_623"></span>[104:2](mhm33.htm#fr_623.md) *Qutrubbul:* A
village situated between Baghdad and ‘Okbara noted for the excellence of
its wine. It was much frequented by the people of the former city in
their parties of pleasure and debauch.

<span id="fn_624"></span>[104:3](mhm33.htm#fr_624.md) *Pickled apples:* Cf.
Qur’án, xx, 25.

<span id="fn_625"></span>[104:4](mhm33.htm#fr_625.md) … *Thou hast gripped
their palate:* Deprived them of realization.

<span id="fn_626"></span>[104:5](mhm33.htm#fr_626.md) *I am of the citizens
of Alexandria:* Metre, *kámil*.

